If you are a shooter this piece is fun, accurate, and beautiful; if you are a collector this 1928, 12-C Grade 3 (Take Down, Target) all original (rear sight might be aftermarket or factory option), excellent condition, blade front sight, Marbles locking tang peep rear sight, mid barrel Marbles Express folding sight, no non factory holes, no tang cracks, octagon barrel, 85% bluing, barrel interior 95%, wood 95%. Steel butt plate, walnut stock. Tube load holds 15 22 shorts, 12 22 longs, 10 22 long rifles. Grandpa bought this in 1929, and carried it on horseback on the Spring Creek Ranch (the old Chisum Pecos Ranch) in New Mexico until 1941. Gave it to my Dad who oiled it up and stuck in closet where it stayed until his death in 2008. I have shot a hundred rounds through it since then shooting Rabbits, Rats, Squirrels, Coyotes, Fixes, Grouse and Crows. Can’t shoot anymore, so hoping to find a home for this with someone who appreciates it’s history. These are selling for between $450.00 for shooters and $1200.00 for collectibles. I believe this gun is both shootable and collectible, I'm asking $650.00 OBO for quick sale. Large pics available via email.........

title: For Sale:  Tactical Defense Norinco SKS Paratrooper + 140 7.62X39 rounds on clips
postcontent:
I set out to create the perfect affordable home defense weapon. For maximun close quarters maneuverability, and ensure reliability I chose a numbers matching action Norinco SKS Paratrooper (16 inch barrel) from 1964 since they were machined at the russian setup factory 26. I then added a folding collapsible stock (comfortable for all from 5'2' to 6'4"), so that it could fit in my nightstand (these stocks are sold out and going for $150 on auction sites. I added M-16/AR-15 style tech-sights, which resulted in 3-3.5 inch groups at 100 yards, which is unheard of for an SKS. I added a compact LED light/laser combo that can be individually operated using your thumb while on the vertical grip, and the laser is adjustable for windage and elevation. I added a vertical grip/bipod which is great for shooting at the range, or close quarters using the laser and flashlight.

Original stock and handguard are included (not pictured), and is setup to accept a paratrooper spike bayonet.
The numbers on the fixed magazine do not match but has been replaced with one from the same factory and time period, and works flawlessly.

This rifle comes with ammo (either impossible to find or overpriced at the moment) for both practice and defense. 50 rds full metal jacket and 90 rds jacketed hollow point on 14 stripper clips.

I am actually selling because my little ones are walking around and getting into stuff, so even with a child lock, we are no longer comfortable keeping a battle rifle in my nightstand. I'll actually look to replace it with a Glock 21 or 22 in an electric lockbox.
I will also include a soft padded bag that has 5 outside pockets for easy access to ammo
This rifle has everything you need for defense and accuracy at an affordable price. Get your SKS before, like AK's and ARs, they become hugely inflated. Everything you need in one affordable package

title: For Sale/Trade:  Daisy Legacy Model 2212 bolt action .22 with original box and manual
postcontent: For sale or trade is my Daisy Legacy Model 2212.  It's a bolt action .22 Long Rifle with a 10-round rotary magazine (similar to a 10/22).  These models have a 19" rifled barrel with an octagon polymer sleeve over it.  This one is in almost new condition, still with the original shipping box, manual, accessory book, and barrel wrench.  I've had it since new in '89, and it has only been shot a couple times over the years.  These are neat little rimfires that were only made from 1988-1990.  This one is a model 2212; and yes, the receiver says 2202.  The receiver was common between the 2201, 2202, and 2212 models.  The only difference between the 2212 and 2202 was the adjustable buttplate.  I will sell if the offer is right, but would rather trade.  Just send me a message.
